The council of Sekhukhune District Municipality convened on Friday April 8. It supported the request by Cllr Julia Lata Mathebe, the executive mayor, to institute a forensic investigation into the affairs of the district municipality. Also read: Arrest successes for Limpopo Highway Patrol Mathebe made the request during a special council meeting that was held in Ga-Nkoana. The forensic investigation was given a six months’ lifespan by council. The purpose of the forensic investigation is to investigate infrastructure, service delivery, governance, organisational capacity and municipal finances.